FOR LINUX (go to this link for windows or mac http://www.tutorialspoint.com/sqlite/sqlite_installation.htm)

sudo get-app install sqlite3

sqlite3 project.db

	.header on			// adds column names
	PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON;	// turns on foreign key constraints (always turn on if inserting)

	// type in the following to create tables
	// the schema can be viewed using the command .schema
	// the schema for a specific table can be viewed using .schema [tablename]

  insert into user values(NULL,'Aaron','Oni','aoni','gainsbruh','aarononi@optusnet.com.au',183,84,'10/12/1994','gain');
  //inserting null into an 'integer primary key' will autoincrement

FOR LINUX  (go to this link for windows or mac http://www.tutorialspoint.com/sqlite/sqlite_perl.htm)

To install the Perl DBI API
$ wget http://search.cpan.org/CPAN/authors/id/T/TI/TIMB/DBI-1.634.tar.gz
$ tar xvfz DBI-1.634.tar.gz
$ cd DBI-1.634
$ perl Makefile.PL
$ make
$ sudo make install


To install SQLite driver for DBI
$ wget http://search.cpan.org/CPAN/authors/id/M/MS/MSERGEANT/DBD-SQLite-1.14.tar.gz
$ tar xvfz DBD-SQLite-1.14.tar.gz
$ cd DBD-SQLite-1.14
$ perl Makefile.PL
$ make
$ sudo make install

To run CGI script locally in ubuntu
sudo get-app install apache2
mv index.cgi /usr/lib/cgi-bin
mv images /var/www/html
mv css /var/www/html
mv fonts /var/www/html
mv js /var/www/html
cd /usr/lib/cgi-bin
chmod +X XXXXX.cgi
sudo a2enmod cgi
sudo service apache2 restart

